<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870331-0138 </DOCNO><HL> Allied-Signal Unit Gets$36.6 Million U.S. Job</HL><DD> 03/31/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ALD CLG HPC GE ETNDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Allied Corp., a unit of Allied-Signal Inc., received a $38.6 million Air Force contract for maintenance equipment for F-15 aircraft avionics.    Hamilton Technology Inc., a unit of Clabir Corp., won a $30.2 million Army contract for munitions fuses.    Hercules Inc. units were awarded contracts totaling $23.5 million to operate a munitions plant at Radford, Va., for the Army and to produce missile rocket motors for the Navy.    Chamberlain Manufacturing Corp., a unit of Duchossois Industries Inc., received a $22.5 million Army contract for munitions parts.    General Electric Co. units were issued Air Force contracts totaling $20.2 million for J-79 aircraft engine parts, F-111 aircraft radar equipment and space satellite storage.    Eaton Corp.'s AIL division received a $15.6 million Air Force contract for B-1B aircraft avionics test equipment. </TEXT></DOC>